```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Int = 3)
    if !(typeof(dt) == DateTime)
        throw(ArgumentError("Input must be of type DateTime."))
    end
    return dt + Duration(bump, "hours")
end
```

This function checks if the input `dt` is of type `DateTime` and throws an error if it's not. It then adds `Duration` equal to `bump` hours to the timestamp. The default value for `bump` is set to 3 hours, which can be overridden by providing a different integer when calling the function.
